commit.message: add newer python versions to ci
no more py2.6 or 3.4, add 3.6 and 3.7.

Allow passing `attr.s` kwargs to the `sumtype` decorator.

And fix our test suite to work with latest attrs, which disabled hashing
by default.

example of calling a match-based function
- also add a ThirdConstructor case in the @match
fix example in README and API documentation to import constructor
use kwargs for attr.ibs instead of two-tuples, since we can rely on the .counter
some more minor changes, hopefully RTD will kick in...
make a trivial change to index.rst to see if it will force updating the API docs
